<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT IN SLAYING ARRESTED AT HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Sun Valley man was arrested early Sunday after police investigating a Los 
Angeles killing traced him to a home on the east side of Moorpark, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. Herb Roper said Steven Batres, 19, of North 
Hollywood was being held on suspicion of murder. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles investigators said Batres is suspected of being one of as many as 
10 people who chased and attacked Ricardo Camacho, 18, as Camacho walked in 
North Hollywood about 11:45 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Police Detective Mike Coffey said the attackers punched and kicked 
Camacho before one of them shot him several times with a handgun. He died 
instantly, Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
Roper said Ventura deputies were called after Los Angeles police got a tip that 
Batres was in Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
He said Batres surrendered peacefully after deputies evacuated nearby homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
