<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAKING PROPOSITION 103 WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Now that the traveling public can see and suffer the full effects, especially 
in the area of pricing inequities, of airline deregulation, why should anyone 
listen to the ideas of Kahn (the "father" of airline deregulation) on how to 
establish insurance rates in California? 
</P>
<P>
Kahn could do us all a favor by concentrating his efforts on helping to solve 
the first deregulatory mess he got us into. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL SHIPMAN 
</P>
<P>
