<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SAN DIEGO STATE WINS WAC BASEBALL CHAMPIONSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego State's 28-6 victory over host Air Force Sunday, combined with 
Wyoming's loss to Colorado State gave the Aztec baseball team the Western 
Athletic Conference championship. 
</P>
<P>
With 28 runs the Aztecs (44-20, 21-7) broke the school record of 27 in a game 
which they set against Colorado State last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU also had 26 RBIs, which broke the school record of 24 set against Fresno 
State in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Barry went four for six with two doubles, a triple, three RBIs and three 
runs scored for SDSU. Teammate Brian Grabeck went three for four with four 
RBIs, five runs scored and a two-run homer. 
</P>
<P>
Air Force finished 25-31, 6-18. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU will play Hawaii in the first round of the WAC tournament at Hawaii on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International lost a doubleheader to host Loyola Marymount. LMU, 43-13 and 
ranked eighth in the nation, won 10-4 and 10-2. Beto Rodriguez hit a home run 
(his 13th) in the first game and went two for four with two RBIs for USIU, 
15-43-1. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego lost to DePauw, 5-1, in the first round of the NCAA Division III 
tournament in Swarthmore, Penn. Senior Tim Ditzler defeated Kyle Gamble, 6-0, 
6-1, for UCSD (12-11). UCSD will play St. John's in the consolation bracket 
today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
