<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: STEPHENS' CONDITION UPGRADED TO SERIOUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hall of Fame trainer Woody Stephens was taken off a respirator Sunday, and his 
condition was upgraded from critical to serious just two days after he 
underwent quadruple heart-bypass surgery, officials in Louisville, Ky., said. 
</P>
<P>
"He's still in the intensive care unit, but the doctor did say he was 
improving," said Pam Greer-Ullrich, a spokeswoman at Norton Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Stephens, 76, has been hospitalized for more than two weeks because of a 
recurrence of chronic breathing problems. He underwent the heart-bypass surgery 
on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
