<HEADLINE>
<P>
DENG MEETS MUBARAK, PROVES HE'S STILL ALIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior leader Deng Xiaoping met Sunday with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak. 
</P>
<P>
It was Deng's first public appearance in three months, dispelling the latest 
rumors of his death. 
</P>
<P>
A Chinese reporter said on condition of anonymity that Deng commented on last 
week's rumor on Asian financial markets that he was dead. "But here I am 
today," he said. 
</P>
<P>
He said Chinese journalists were told not to report on the meeting. The 
national television news failed to mention it, the first time it has ever been 
known to keep silent on a meeting between Deng and a visiting head of state. 
</P>
<P>
However, the official New China News Agency issued a brief report, saying Deng 
met Mubarak "as his old friend." 
</P>
