<P>
Video works by artist Ilene Segalove, now featured in her first career survey 
at the Laguna Art Museum, will be shown June 1 on KCET Channel 28 in 
conjunction with the exhibit. The 30-minute program, titled "The Eleventh 
Hour," is sub-titled "Why I Got Into TV and Other Stories." Segalove is 
well-known for humorous videos and radio works about television and other 
aspects of popular culture. 
