<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNMEN KILL 4 IN REPUTED TEXAS GAMBLING CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FT. WORTH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of masked men opened fire in a cafe today, killing four people and 
wounding three while customers gambled in a game "possibly involving tens of 
thousands of dollars," police said. 
</P>
<P>
The intruders reportedly burst into the Glass Key Cafe and yelled "task force" 
before they began firing automatic weapons. 
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Doug Clarke said there were conflicting reports from witnesses 
but there apparently were four to six gunmen, some wearing masks and some in 
camouflage gear. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the Glass Key is a suspected center for illegal gambling. About 15 
people were inside at the time of the 7 a.m. shooting. 
</P>
<P>
"It has been known to have gambling and dice games there," Clarke said. 
"There's also dope dealing in and around the area." 
</P>
<P>
Police Chief Thomas Wyndom said authorities "believe there was a game going on 
possibly involving tens of thousands of dollars." 
</P>
</TEXT>
