<TEXT>
<P>
A former basketball player at Fresno State who was shot in the leg during a 
dispute over use of a telephone was reported in stable condition today. 
</P>
<P>
Andre Sims, 23, was taken to Valley Medical Center after he was wounded 
Saturday afternoon at a motel. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Sims' assailant fired four shots, and one struck Sims in the upper 
thigh. The assailant was not captured. 
</P>
<P>
Sims played for the Bulldogs in his freshman and sophomore seasons before 
leaving the team. 
</P>
