<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIELDY SCORES 1 1/4-LENGTH WIN AT BELMONT PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fernwood Stables' Fieldy circled the field on the turn and drew away in the 
final yards for a 1 1/4-length victory over Summer Secretary in Sunday's 
$87,900 Beaugay Handicap at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
Fieldy, sent off under jockey Craig Perret as the betting favorite in the field 
of five fillies and mares ages 3 and up, won for the second time in five starts 
this year. 
</P>
<P>
The Irish-bred 7-year-old mare by Northfields out of Gramy earned $52,740 and 
returned $4.40, $2.60 and $2.20. 
</P>
<P>
Summer Secretary paid $3 and $2.20 and Lady Talc, another six lengths back in 
third, paid $2.40. 
</P>
</TEXT>
